$ASTS will be providing add-on service for as little as $1/month for the 1.3b existing customers acquired through agreements with wireless service providers (Vodafone and AT&T). 

There are still 4 billion (3.3 billion w/out broadband and 700 million without phone/internet access) people without access to internet/phone service. SpaceMobile will be their only option and the most efficient way to deploy coverage worldwide. Capturing this business presents tremendous growth potential for SpaceMobile. 

At $1/month, this untapped revenue stream could potentially be $48b annually. The existing customer base of 1.3b subscribers would provide a maximum annual revenue of $15.6b. Total of $63.6b maximum annual revenue, once fully deployed (ignoring revenue sharing agreements). 

The NPA valuation model included in the investor presentation (1.4x EV) uses a maximum revenue of $16b in 2030. 

There is potential for this to be bigger than their valuation model. Bullish
